[0.6, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[1.0, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1mOpenFable\u001b[0m  ·  MCP Demo\r\n"]
[1.4, "o", "  \u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.6, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[33m❯\u001b[0m  Ingesting: Project Chimera Q1 2026 Research Report\r\n"]
[5.8, "o", "     \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mf48791ab-b507-4b31-9799-9388378148f2\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.0, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[33m❯\u001b[0m  Ingesting: Independent Risk & Safety Audit (Q2 2026)\r\n"]
[8.2, "o", "     \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m536e76a8-3bb2-44da-b9a4-ea5164d7518e\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.2, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1;36myou\u001b[0m  Using the query tool with token_budget=4000, compare Project Chimera's\r\n       Q1 2026 latency figures with the findings in the independent risk audit.\r\n       Are there any contradictions? What are the implications for the Q4 target?\r\n"]
[15.8, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[32m◆\u001b[0m  The 12 ms anaesthetized figure is confirmed by both documents.\r\n"]
[16.4, "o", "     But the audit measured \u001b[1m31 ms\u001b[0m on awake subjects — a 2.6× gap\r\n"]
[17.0, "o", "     the Q1 report never discloses in its executive summary.\r\n"]
[19.0, "o", "\r\n     The Q4 sub-5 ms target is highly aggressive: requires the Phase 3\r\n     ASIC \u001b[1mand\u001b[0m a motion-compensation algorithm not yet in development.\r\n"]
[26.0, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1;36myou\u001b[0m  Using the query tool with token_budget=150, what were the exact\r\n       measurement conditions used to obtain the 12 ms latency figure in\r\n       the Q1 report?\r\n"]
[29.0, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[32m◆\u001b[0m  All figures obtained under isoflurane anaesthesia (1.5–2.0% v/v)\r\n"]
[30.0, "o", "     using a stereotaxic frame. \u001b[1mNOT\u001b[0m taken from freely-moving or awake subjects.\r\n"]
[31.6, "o", "\r\n     \u001b[2m(§2.2.1 — three headings deep — retrieved in only 150 tokens.)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[38.6, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1;36myou\u001b[0m  Using the query tool with token_budget=2000, what were the exact\r\n       measurement conditions used to obtain the 12 ms latency figure in\r\n       the Q1 report, and what broader context surrounds that methodology?\r\n"]
[41.6, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[32m◆\u001b[0m  Same anaesthesia protocol — but now with surrounding context:\r\n"]
[42.2, "o", "     the Q4 target \u001b[1mexplicitly\u001b[0m requires awake-subject calibration.\r\n"]
[42.8, "o", "     The 12 ms baseline is not directly comparable to the sub-5 ms goal.\r\n"]
[49.8, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1;36myou\u001b[0m  Using the query tool with token_budget=2000, what animal species\r\n       other than mice have been used in Project Chimera trials, and what\r\n       were their results?\r\n"]
[52.8, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[32m◆\u001b[0m  Only murine (mouse) subjects appear in either document.\r\n"]
[53.5, "o", "     No other species are mentioned in the corpus.\r\n"]
[55.4, "o", "\r\n     \u001b[2m(No hallucination — the agent reports what the documents contain.)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[63.4, "o", ""]
